body_html:
Everything's fine, I've got them all here: https://github.com/markdaoust/tensorflow/tree/pr16817

I was trying to fix the test errors and issued the wrong push command and pushed tensorflow/master to your master instead of the pr branch. That killed the PR, and then locked me out of your branch so I can't fix it.

The commits are all intact, if you pull from my branch and reopen this (or a new pr) everything should be right back where it was.

Or I can push my branch as a new PR (they're still all marked as your commits).

Sorry for the confusion. How should we go about fixing this?
